## What changed

Adds `tools/doc-objects/aggregate-release-digest.sh`, the read side of the doc-object pattern.
Given a commit range (`<FROM>..<TO>`) and an optional `--audience` (`customer|internal|all`)
filter, it walks commits with `git rev-list --reverse`, reads each commit's doc-object from the
`refs/notes/doc-objects` git-notes ref, parses the `audience` field out of the note frontmatter
with awk, and emits a single markdown bundle meant as LLM input for release-notes synthesis.
Commits with no attached note are skipped and counted; notes whose audience does not match the
filter (and are not `both`) are filtered out. A trailing HTML comment reports
included/filtered/missing counts.

## Risk / watch

Pure additive tooling — a standalone bash script under `tools/`, not wired into any build,
runtime, or product code path. Consumers must first run
`git fetch origin refs/notes/doc-objects:refs/notes/doc-objects` for the notes to be visible.
The script runs under `set -euo pipefail`; the audience filter defaults to `customer` when
`--audience` is omitted. No epic matched (dotcms-aios epic index was not reachable).
